description:
''This was undoubtedly one of the most enthralling churches we visited in Ethiopia. The church is still in use and monks are often present in their yellow garb.

Appealing as it is on the outside with its stone walls, arched doors, and two-tiered thatch roof, it's the inner sanctuary of Debre Berhan Selassie, with its glorious frescos, that really shines.
It stands in its own enclosure surrounded by a wall with twelve small towers. Trees provide shade. The church is notable for seven ostrich eggs on a medallion that is on the roof. ''

📍 Debre Birhan Selassie, Gondar, Ethiopia

description:
Aydee Chambalala!

Inscribed in 2015 on the Representative List of the Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity, Fichee-Chambalaalla is a New Year festival celebrated among the Sidama people of Ethiopia. According to the oral tradition, Fichee commemorates a Sidama woman who visited her parents and relatives once a year after her marriage, bringing buurisame, a meal prepared from false banana, milk, and butter shared with neighbors. Fichee has since become a unifying symbol of the Sidama people. Each year, astrologers determine the correct date for the festival, which is then announced to the clans. Communal events take place throughout the festival, including traditional songs and dances. Every member participates irrespective of age, gender, and social status.
#LandOfOrigins #VisitEthiopia #Chambalaalla
caption: Aydee Chambalala!

description:
Bata LeMariam: A Mesmerizing Historical gem that lies in the heart of Addis Ababa

Located adjacent to the Grand Palace and built between 1918-1927 by empress Zewditu to memorize her father Menilik ll on the 14th anniversary of his death; Beata Lemariam church houses numerous manuscripts, robes of Menilik and Zewditu, icons, and other ecclesiastic and secular objects of great historical and spiritual significance.

The construction was made using medieval age construction technology. There are symbols of M (representing Menilik) on the walls. Beyond that, the church's top dome is crowned with Meniliks crown while other churches' domes are crowned with crosses. The mausoleum keeps the remains of Emperor Menelik II and Iyasu V and Empress Zewditu and Taytu.

#Landoforigins #Visitethiopia #Addisababa #beatalemraiam #ethiopianchurch
caption: Bata LeMariam: A Mesmerizing Historical gem that lies in the heart of Addis Ababa!

description:
Step into an adventurous trip to Ethiopia and make your trip beyond a mere sightseeing. Socialize with and be a part of the culture and way of life of the host community.

When you visit the south and southwestern part of Ethiopia it’s almost impossible, at least to taste kocho /a food made of enset, the 'false banana'/ once. But never stop with only eating. Try to be the part of the preparation process. It will be a lifetime experience.

description:
visit Omo Valley and Challenge your perception of beauty!

Living along the east banks of the Omo River in southern Ethiopia, the karos are one of the smallest tribes in the region. A visit to this part of Ethiopia will help you to capture the splendor of Karo’s tribe makeup skill.

Decorating their faces and bodies with chalk and ochre serves various purposes, including enhancing the chance of finding love, and intimidating rivals.

description:
🌳 ''Ethiopia’s northern highlands were one continuous forest, but over time that forest has been continually bisected, eaten up by agriculture and the pressures of a growing population. Less than three percent of primary forest remains. And nearly all of that three percent was only found in forests protected by the Ethiopian Orthodox church.''

📍 Ethiopian Orthodox church in the southern part of Gondar, Ethiopia.
